description:
NLT TPO (T12, T13, T14, T15 - Lime) (T16 - Ash)
T2: Ash - Remove all major deadwood from the crown; Reduce the low subsiding branch growing to the south; Reduce the low branch growing to the north-east by 2m;
T23: Large Lime - Cut the entire tree down ground level; 
T24: Lime - Reduce the height by 5-6m; Reduce the crown spread to balance and shape; Remove all major deadwood from the crown;
T26: Lime - Crown reduce the height back to previous reduction points; Reduce the crown spread to balance and shape; Remove all major deadwood from the crown; 
T27: Large Lime - Sparse foliage and major deadwood in crown; Reduce the entire tree down to a height of 8m - Reason: There is decay on the compression side (south side of the trunk) at the base

T3: Large twin-stem Hawthorn - Cut the entire tree down to fence/ hedge height;
T4: Small Ivy Clad Hawthorn - Cut the entire tree down to fence / hedge height;
Small Elder - (Situated in neighbouring land) - Cut back from Church hall;
T8: Old Hawthorn - Reduce the 3 above stems by 2-2.Sm; 
T11: Elderberry - Cut the entire tree to ground level;
T12:Yew - Remove low branches to a height of 1.6-1.Sm for access around the tree;
T13: Chestnut - Reduce the 3 low branches overhanging the Church Yard by 2.5-3m; Remove all major deadwood from the crown
